rns.\n* [[M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce]] - ''[[Girls, Girls, Girls (M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce album)|Girls, Girls, Girls]]'' peaked at No. 2 in the ''Billboard'' charts.\n* The show ''[[Headbangers Ball]]'' debuts on [[MTV]] on April 18, 1987.\n* [[Bon Jovi]]'s album ''[[Slippery When Wet]]'' tops the Billboard charts for eight weeks.\n* In December 1987, M\u00f6tley Cr\u00fce [[bassist]] [[Nikki Sixx]] suffers a near-fatal heroin overdose.\n* Bassist [[Louiche Mayorga]] leaves [[Suicidal Tendencies]] and is replaced by Bob Heathcote. At the same time, the band becomes a five piece as they hire former [[No Mercy (metal band)|No Mercy]] guitarist [[Mike Clark (guitarist)|Mike Clark]] as their rhythm guitarist.\n\n{{S-start}}\n{{Timeline box|title=[[Timeline of heavy metal music|Heavy Metal Timeline]]|before=[[1986 in heavy metal music|1986]]|after=[[1988 in heavy metal music|1988]]|year='''1987'''}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Timeline of heavy metal and hard rock music}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1987 In Heavy Metal Music}}\n[[Category:1980s in heavy metal music]]\n[[Category:1987 in music|Metal]]\n", "text_old": "{{Year in music|1987}}\n{{Year nav topic5|1987|heavy metal music}}\n{{unreferenced|date=October 2016}}\nThis is a timeline documenting the events of [[Heavy Metal music|heavy metal]] in the year 1987.\n\n==Newly formed bands==\n*[[Alchemist (band)|Alchemist]] \n*[[Alice in Chains]]\n* [[Asphyx]]\n* [[Autopsy (band)|Autopsy]]\n*[[Cynic (band)|Cynic]]\n*[[Danzig (band)|Danzig]]\n*[[Deicide (band)|Deicide]]\n*[[Disharmonic Orchestra]]\n*[[Entombed (band)|Entombed]]\n*[[Follow for Now]]\n*[[Herm\u00e9tica]]\n*[[Hobbs' Angel of Death]]\n*[[Impellitteri]]\n*[[Intruder (American band)|Intruder]]\n*[[Malevolent Creation]]\n*[[Meliah Rage]]\n* [[Meshuggah]]\n*[[Mortification (band)|Mortification]]\n* [[Nirvana (band)|Nirvana]]\n*[[Nocturnus]]\n* [[Phantom Blue]]\n* [[Pink Cream 69]]\n* [[Primordial (band)|Primordial]]\n*[[Ripping Corpse]]\n* [[Rollins Band]]\n*[[Rotting Christ]]\n*[[Samael (band)|S